Utilization:
NOT AVBL FOR TFC
BLW FL315 AT (ERKIR DCT KPT) EXC ARR (LSZH, LSMD) & VIA ERKIR AND-THEN VIA EDUUCHI1K & ABV FL315 AT ERKIR
Operational Goal:
Standard option ARR LSZH, LSMD via ERKIR which have to file upper RFL above FL315 for the transfer LOVVACC to EDUUUAC. The lower MIN FL (vertical x border DCT with Munich ACC) shall allow shallow vertical trajectories calculated by NM in the vicinity of KPT. 
Traffic intending to descend early below EDUUUTA (triggered by a lower RFL below FL315 before or at ERKIR), shall be rejected and need to file ERKIR L608 KPT, which is limited to max FL315 (descend before ERKIR is required). Different routings (low and high) will support ATM system LOVV to select the correct downstream center (EDUUUAC above FL315 or EDMMACC below FL315).

COMPULSORY FOR TFC
RFL BLW FL245
DEP (ENBR, ENZV)
WITH ARR EGNT 
(EXC VIA CUTEL DCT GOMOT DUE TO  EGD513 ACTIVATION)
Time Availability: Outside the activated vertical limits of EGD613D/EGD514/EGD514Z
Operational Goal:
There is no reasonable alternative route that can be flight planned.
To force traffic onto a shorter route. When EGD613D is promulgated active in the AUP/UUP at the filed FL and alternative routing NIVUN DCT LAMRO DCT CUTEL DCT NATEB is unavailable due D513 activity traffic may file via CUTEL DCT GOMOT. AOs are advised to check NOTAMs for D513 activity. Traffic filing CUTEL DCT GOMOT is exempt from this restriction.
Traffic is not forced to use this DCT if there is activity promulgated in EGD613D or EGD514/EGD514Z.
See associated LAMRO DCT CUTEL, CUTEL DCT NATEB RADs.
